One-time Firebase setup (do this first)
1. Create the Firebase project
Go to console.firebase.google.com → Add project → name it dindos-restaurant. Then inside the project enable:

Authentication → Sign-in method → Email/Password → Enable
Firestore Database → Create database → Start in test mode → pick a region (e.g. asia-southeast1)
Storage → Get started → test mode
2. Open a PowerShell terminal in your project folder and run these four commands in order:


# Add flutterfire to PATH (only needed once)
[Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable("Path", $env:Path + ";C:\Users\justi\AppData\Local\Pub\Cache\bin", "User")
Close PowerShell, reopen it, then:


# Log in to Firebase (opens browser)
firebase login

# Connect your Flutter project to Firebase (interactive — pick your project + Android)
cd C:\Users\justi\CapstoneYawa
flutterfire configure

# Run the app
flutter run

